A tangent to a curve at a point is a straight line that touches the curve at only that point. In the diagram on the right, straight line
is a tangent to the curve
What method can be used to find the gradient of the tangent to the curve
at other points on the curve, such as

(3, 9)? 

Using a graph to obtain the gradient can be difficult and also inaccurate. There are other methods to find the gradient of the curve at a particular point, that is by using the idea of limits as in the discovery activity below.
